<task id="task_FE6BEB3A1264493A9E9A4CFC5023CCA9">
  <title>Create a Single Mbox</title>
  <shortdesc>Many people place a single mbox on a page to display an offer. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <steps id="steps_13272BC879FA4609921ECD04680BAD7C">
      <step id="step_2C17F06715854935A78B6CA7532FC48F">
        <cmd>Make sure the Web page contains a 
			 <xref href="t_Referencing_mboxjs.xml#task_4A321498EDAF4A048E3B9A74FD9E67E9" type="task" format="dita" scope="local">reference to 
				<filepath>mbox.js</filepath></xref> in the head. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_9F7C3103C5554B11ABE9B2BEFB5542D9">
        <cmd>In the body of the HTML page where you want to insert an mbox,
			 define the beginning and end of the 
			 <xref href="c_About_Default_Content.xml#concept_EDDC6DA0DC6942A79393F63F27C29140" type="concept" format="dita" scope="local">default content</xref>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_B532C88FA954459A8EF326B70B52CB73">
        <cmd>Immediately follow the default content 
			 <codeph>&lt;/div&gt;</codeph> with the 
			 <codeph>mboxCreate</codeph> function. 
		  </cmd>
        <info>
          <p>
            <note>Because the 
				  <codeph>mboxCreate()</codeph> function locates the content it
				  will replace by searching just above itself in the DOM for 
				  <codeph>&lt;div class="mboxDefault"&gt;</codeph>, it is critical
				  that no other HTML be inserted between the close 
				  <codeph>&lt;/div&gt;</codeph> tag and the 
				  <codeph>mboxCreate()</codeph> function. 
				</note>
          </p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step id="step_C4A4C9E28EE945509B970468B2284086">
        <cmd>Give the mbox a unique name which makes sense for your campaign
			 strategy and company procedures. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>Mbox names can be up to 255 characters long. 
			 </p>
          <p>In the example below, the mbox is named myMbox. 
			 </p>
          <p>Example of Javascript for Basic Mbox: 
			 </p>
          <p>
            <table id="table_839A240B5B2F4EF5996F24CCBC75B036">
              <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col01" colnum="1" colwidth="1.00*" />
                <colspec colnum="2" colname="col1" colwidth="1.17*" />
                <thead>
                  <row>
                    <entry colname="col01">Before 
						</entry>
                    <entry colname="col1">After 
						</entry>
                  </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <row>
                    <entry colname="col01">
                      <p>
                        <codeblock outputclass="syntax html">&lt;head&gt;

 

&lt;/head&gt;

&lt;body&gt;
My existing page.
Part that I'd like to overlay during a campaign or test.
&lt;/body&gt;</codeblock>
                      </p>
                    </entry>
                    <entry colname="col1">
                      <p>
                        <codeblock outputclass="syntax html">
                          <codeph>&lt;head&gt;
</codeph>
&lt;script
src="http://www.mycompany.com/​​​myfolder​/mbox.js"
type="text/javascript"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;

&lt;body&gt;
 My existing page.​&lt;div class="mboxDefault"&gt;
 Part that I'd like to overlay during a campaign or test.
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;
 mboxCreate('myMbox');
&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
</codeblock>
                      </p>
                    </entry>
                  </row>
                </tbody>
              </tgroup>
            </table>
          </p>
          <p>
            <b>Tips:</b>
          </p>
          <p>
            <ul id="ul_E40E64A1301844629B16AF3EB03FF65E">
              <li id="li_9BD66F756D95406188212D08954C8489"> When inserting an
				  mbox, do not add or remove cells or rows from tables. Where possible, wrap only
				  the contents of table cells or whole table. 
				</li>
              <li id="li_BC3DCF8235474F6B81E2B16D4CDDB42C"> Do not use mboxes to
				  remove inputs from forms. Mboxes are only capable of hiding or showing content.
				  They do not remove nodes from the DOM. 
				</li>
              <li id="li_E5B84093A22D4D2EAED2710E2143445C"> Where possible, wrap
				  only paragraphs, not individual words. 
				</li>
              <li id="li_3FB7E1C3195846C981059196ABF9E90F"> Mbox names are case
				  sensitive. Mymbox and myMbox will be recognized as two different mboxes. 
				</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_1B75F865E88A40A5AB75442CF6059FEF">
        <cmd>Browse to the page with the mbox and ensure there are no errors. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_4E4A2A44B24144D697F8B840ED31C1C6">
        <cmd>
          <xref href="t_Validating_an_Mbox.xml#task_4BB8E090CBBF4C56A39BB63BF1ADB964" type="task" format="dita" scope="local">Validate the mbox</xref>. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_CB3EC84665224A5CA03117AFC5705772">
        <cmd>Ensure the mbox is listed in the mbox list for your account. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
